.Dd $Mdocdate: July 30 2022 $
.Dt MKFIFO 1
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm mkfifo
.Nd make FIFOs
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm mkfifo
.Op Fl m Ar mode
.Ar fifo_name ...
.Sh DESCRIPTION
.Nm mkfifo
creates the FIFOs requested, in the order specified,
using mode 0666
modified by the current
.Xr umask 2 .
It requires write permission in the parent directory.
.Pp
The options are as follows:
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It Fl m Ar mode
Set the file permission bits of newly created FIFOs to
.Ar mode .
The mode argument can be in any of the formats specified to the
.Xr chmod 1
utility.
If a symbolic mode is specified, the operators
.Ql +
and
.Ql -
are interpreted relative to an initial mode of
.Dq a=rw .
.El
.Sh EXIT STATUS
.Ex -std mkfifo
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr mkdir 1 ,
.Xr rm 1 ,
.Xr mkfifo 2 ,
.Xr mknod 8
.Sh STANDARDS
The
.Nm
utility is compliant with the
.St -p1003.1-2008
specification.
.Sh HISTORY
The
.Nm
command appeared in
.Bx 4.3 Reno .
